      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>One of the steps in fat metabolism is the hydration of crotonate to yield 3-hydroxybutyrate. The reaction occurs by addition of  – OH to the Si face at C3, followed by protonation at C2, also from the Si face. Draw the product of the reaction, showing the stereochemistry of each step.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBb3dSIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--1383713f37d644b027ccff447470a3377352141e/OChem_05_EC_022.jpg\" alt=\"The figure shows a reaction where crotonate converts to 3-hydroxybutyrate. In crotonate, the double bond is between C2 and C3.\">",
